=head1 DESCRIPTION

Contains information about the specified configurable setting for a
directory.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AllowedValues => Str

The valid range of values for the directory setting. These values
depend on the C<DataType> of your directory.


=head2 AppliedValue => Str

The value of the directory setting that is applied to the directory.


=head2 DataType => Str

The data type of a directory setting. This is used to define the
C<AllowedValues> of a setting. For example a data type can be
C<Boolean>, C<DurationInSeconds>, or C<Enum>.


=head2 LastRequestedDateTime => Str

The date and time when the request to update a directory setting was
last submitted.


=head2 LastUpdatedDateTime => Str

The date and time when the directory setting was last updated.


=head2 Name => Str

The name of the directory setting. For example:

C<TLS_1_0>


=head2 RequestDetailedStatus => L<Paws::DS::DirectoryConfigurationSettingRequestDetailedStatus>

Details about the status of the request to update the directory
setting. If the directory setting is deployed in more than one region,
status is returned for the request in each region where the setting is
deployed.


=head2 RequestedValue => Str

The value that was last requested for the directory setting.


=head2 RequestStatus => Str

The overall status of the request to update the directory setting
request. If the directory setting is deployed in more than one region,
and the request fails in any region, the overall status is C<Failed>.


=head2 RequestStatusMessage => Str

The last status message for the directory status request.


=head2 Type => Str

The type, or category, of a directory setting. Similar settings have
the same type. For example, C<Protocol>, C<Cipher>, or
C<Certificate-Based Authentication>.



